  "prompt": "How do you know who viewed you video on Instagram?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, Instagram offers different levels of visibility into who views your videos, depending on the type of content you\u2019ve posted. Here's a breakdown of how you can see who has viewed your videos on various parts of Instagram:\n\n### 1. **Instagram Stories**\n**How to See Viewers:**\n- **Open Your Story:** Tap your profile picture at the top of the Instagram home screen to view your active Story.\n- **Swipe Up or Tap the Viewers Icon:** While viewing your Story, swipe up on the screen or tap the eye icon at the bottom to see a list of all usernames who have viewed your Story.\n\n**Notes:**\n- **Visibility Duration:** Stories are visible for 24 hours unless you save them as Highlights.\n- **Refresh Report:** The viewer list updates in real-time as people watch your Story.\n\n### 2. **Instagram Reels**\n**How to See Viewers:**\n- **View Count:** Under each Reel, you'll see a view count indicating how many times it has been watched.\n- **Interactions:** You can see who has liked, commented, or shared your Reel, which provides some insight into engaged viewers.\n\n**Notes:**\n- **No Detailed Viewer List:** Unlike Stories, Reels do not provide a list of individual viewers. Instagram prioritizes aggregate view counts over specific viewer information for Reels.\n\n### 3. **IGTV Videos**\n**How to See Viewers:**\n- **View Count:** Similar to Reels, IGTV videos display the total number of views.\n- **Engagement Insights:** You can see who has liked or commented on your IGTV videos.\n\n**Notes:**\n- **No Specific Viewer Data:** Instagram does not provide a detailed list of individual viewers for IGTV videos.\n\n### 4. **Feed Videos (Standard Posts)**\n**How to See Viewers:**\n- **View Count:** Videos posted to your main Instagram feed show a view count below the post.\n- **Engagement Indicators:** You can see who has liked or commented on your video.\n\n**Notes:**\n- **No Viewer List:** Instagram does not offer a feature to see exactly who has watched your feed videos, only the total number of views.\n\n### 5. **Live Videos**\n**How to See Viewers:**\n- **During Live Broadcast:** You can see the usernames of people watching your live video in real-time.\n- **Post-Live Insights:** After the broadcast, you may have access to some analytics about viewer engagement, but not a complete list of all viewers.\n\n**Notes:**\n- **Engagement Features:** Viewers can interact via comments and reactions, providing insight into who is watching and actively engaging.\n\n### **Important Considerations:**\n\n- **Privacy Settings:** Your ability to see who views your content can be affected by your privacy settings. Ensure your account is set to private or public based on your preference for audience visibility.\n  \n- **Third-Party Apps Caution:** Be wary of third-party applications or services that claim to provide detailed viewer information. These are often scams and can compromise your account security.\n\n- **Updates and Changes:** Instagram frequently updates its platform. For the most current features related to video views and analytics, check Instagram\u2019s official [Help Center](https://help.instagram.com/) or the latest app updates.\n\n### **Maximizing Your Insights:**\n\n- **Use Instagram Insights:** If you have a **Business** or **Creator** account, Instagram Insights provides more detailed analytics about your content performance, including demographics of your audience and engagement metrics.\n  \n- **Engage with Your Audience:** Encouraging likes, comments, and shares can help you identify active viewers and build a more engaged community around your videos.\n\n### **Final Thoughts:**\n\nWhile Instagram provides various tools to gauge the performance and engagement of your videos, it limits direct access to specific viewer lists for most video types to protect user privacy. Utilizing the available metrics and fostering engagement through interactive content can help you understand and grow your audience effectively.\n\nIf there have been significant updates or changes to these features after October 2023, I recommend consulting Instagram\u2019s official resources or exploring the app\u2019s latest features directly.",
